## Maven Assignment 1
### What is the difference between Maven and Gradle

Maven is based on developing purely on the java language based software
while,

Gradles is based on developing domain specific language for creating speific project structures.


Gradles provide customize dependencies selection and substitute rules that can be declared and handle unwanted dependenceis project

Maven allows one to overide dependencies.but only by version

Maven uses XML

Gradle does not use XML

Maven allows compilation, distribution, documentation and team collaboration

Maven repository is a directory of packaged JAR file with pom.xml file

Gradle uses Directed Acyclic Graph to determine the order to run the tasks.

Gradle default build tool is Andriod OS
